==French==
===Etymology===
Vulgar Latin ''*retenīre'', from classical Latin ''[[retinere]]'', from ''[[re-]]'' + ''[[tenere|tenēre]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʀətəniʀ/}}

===Verb===
'''retenir'''

# {{transitive}} to [[hold back]], rein in
# {{transitive}} to [[keep]], [[detain]], [[hold up]]
# {{transitive}} to [[retain]], [[hold]]
# {{reflexive}} to restrain oneself, [[hold back]]

